
Ingredients:

Pizza dough
1 cup tomato sauce
2 cups shredded mozzarella cheese
Pepperoni slices
Dried oregano
Instructions:
Preheat your oven to 450°F (230°C).
Roll out the pizza dough and place it on a pizza stone or baking sheet.
Spread the tomato sauce evenly over the dough.
Sprinkle the shredded mozzarella cheese over the sauce.
Arrange the pepperoni slices on top of the cheese.
Sprinkle dried oregano over the pizza.
Bake in the preheated oven for 12-15 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown and the cheese is melted and bubbly.
Remove from the oven and let it cool for a few minutes before slicing and serving.
